======================================================================
N_3(0) = #{(s1,s2,s3) Ôłł QR┬│ : s1+s2+s3 Ôëí 0 mod p}
======================================================================

PROOF (via Gauss sums):

Let ¤ç = Legendre symbol mod p, G = Gauss sum = ╬ú_{aÔëá0} ¤ç(a) ╬Â^a.
For p Ôëí 3 mod 4: G┬▓ = -p.

╬ú_{sÔłłQR} ╬Â^{ts} = (¤ç(t)┬ĚG - 1) / 2

N_3(0) = (1/p) ╬ú_t (╬ú_{sÔłłQR} ╬Â^{ts})┬│
       = m┬│/p + (1/8p) ╬ú_{tÔëá0} (¤ç(t)G - 1)┬│

Expanding:
  (¤ç(t)G - 1)┬│ = ¤ç(t)┬│G┬│ - 3¤ç(t)┬▓G┬▓ + 3¤ç(t)G - 1

Summing over t Ôëá 0:
  ╬ú ¤ç(t)┬│ = ╬ú ¤ç(t) = 0     (since ¤ç┬│ = ¤ç)
  ╬ú ¤ç(t)┬▓ = ╬ú 1 = p-1       (since ¤ç┬▓ = 1)
  ╬ú ¤ç(t) = 0

So ╬ú_{tÔëá0} (¤ç(t)G-1)┬│ = -3G┬▓(p-1) - (p-1) = (p-1)(3p-1)

N_3(0) = m┬│/p + (p-1)(3p-1)/(8p)
       = [(p-1)┬│ + (p-1)(3p-1)] / (8p)
       = (p-1)(p┬▓+p) / (8p)
       = (p┬▓-1)/8
       = m(m+1)/2  Ôťô  (since m = (p-1)/2)

Computational verification of N_3(0):
  P_7 (m=3): N_3(0) = 6, m(m+1)/2 = 6, match = True
  P_11 (m=5): N_3(0) = 15, m(m+1)/2 = 15, match = True
  P_19 (m=9): N_3(0) = 45, m(m+1)/2 = 45, match = True
  P_23 (m=11): N_3(0) = 66, m(m+1)/2 = 66, match = True
  P_31 (m=15): N_3(0) = 120, m(m+1)/2 = 120, match = True
  P_43 (m=21): N_3(0) = 231, m(m+1)/2 = 231, match = True

